<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8713] Make groovy osgi plugin extensible to be able to use it in eclipse target platform</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8713</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since 2.5, groovy is provided through modules only (the groovy-all jar has been removed)&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The core module is groovy.jar, then additional modules like groovy-json are osgi fragment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently these cannot be really used in&#160;eclipse target platform, because classes exported by fragment are not visible by PDE.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding &lt;b&gt;Eclipse-ExtensibleAPI: true&lt;/b&gt; to the groovy.jar manifest would solve that issue. This header is only used by PDE, it has no impact on osgi runtime.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
